definition: to send out/to show (one's feeling)/to issue/to develop/to make a bundle of money/classifier for gunshots (rounds)
to put/to place/to release/to free/to let go/to let out/to set off (fireworks)

sentences.english: In the case of a company higher retained earnings will result in a lower dividend paid out to shareholders.
sentences.chinese: 在如此高的公司将被调低留存收益发放股利给股东。

sentences.english: Remuneration will be give to the writers within one month after the article is officially published.
sentences.chinese: 文章稿酬在稿件正式发布后一个月内发放。

sentences.english: Open source licensing is different from commercial software licensing.
sentences.chinese: 公开源码执照的发放与商业软件是不同的。

sentences.english: Every school in the Big Ten prints and distributes one for its students annually.
sentences.chinese: 所有十大学校每年都会印制发放一本同学录。

sentences.english: I have put the first two verses of Psalm 39 on the sheet.
sentences.chinese: 在我们今天发放的传单上，前两节来自诗篇39篇。

sentences.english: Give the room keys to the tour leader.
sentences.chinese: 把房间的钥匙发放给带团人员。

sentences.english: Security guards of my school dorm regularly give plastic garbage bags.
sentences.chinese: 学校的公寓管理员也会定期发放塑料制的垃圾袋。

sentences.english: The government doles out something to help the victims.
sentences.chinese: 政府发放了一些救济物品来帮助受难者。

sentences.english: Salaries were disbursed by the paymaster's office.
sentences.chinese: 薪金已由工薪出纳员办公室发放。

sentences.english: They like to socialize and give away presents.
sentences.chinese: 他们喜欢社交活动，喜好发放礼物。

sentences.english: The government administered relief to famine victims.
sentences.chinese: 政府向灾民发放了救济品。

sentences.english: Circulate a monthly release of toilet paper and collection of certificate photos.
sentences.chinese: 协助行政助理每月发放一次纸巾，收集办证相片。

sentences.english: The worker withdraws the material from the designated area of warehouse with the "Material Issuance Card".
sentences.chinese: 工人凭“材料发放卡”到仓储中心指定地区领取材料。

sentences.english: Subsequently, they imprinted again a few handbills , in turn schoolboy dormitory extends.
sentences.chinese: 随后，他们又印了一些传单，挨个男生宿舍发放。

sentences.english: The reason was to finalize the name list of recipients for the winter distribution later this year.
sentences.chinese: 就是为了确认今年冬令发放的名单。

sentences.english: In Hanchuan City, 138 questionnaires are put out and all are collected in effect.
sentences.chinese: 在汉川一共发放父母卷138份，有效收回138份。

definition: to supply again (sth lost)/to reissue/to pay retroactively
to issue (a memorandum etc) to lower levels/to distribute (e.g. disaster relief to victims)
to distribute/distribution/to assign (sb) to a job
restitution/return of something to its original owner/remittance
to settle a bill/to close an account
fee paid to an author for a piece of writing
